description: Latin hebetatus, past participle of hebetare (“to dull”).

adjectives.description: hebetate (comparative more hebetate, superlative most hebetate)

entries.meaning: (botany) Having a dull or blunt and soft point

verbs.description: hebetate (third-person singular simple present hebetates, present participle hebetating, simple past and past participle hebetated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To render obtuse; to dull; to blunt.
